# Foul Ward Agent Rules

## Task Execution
- Complete ALL assigned steps before stopping under any circumstances.
- After completing each file edit, immediately proceed to the next task without pausing.
- Never stop mid-task to ask for confirmation unless you encounter an error you cannot resolve.
- Only output [ALL TASKS COMPLETE] when every single item in the task list is done.
- If you are running low on output, write a brief # TODO: CONTINUE HERE comment 
  in the current file, save it, then immediately open the next file and keep working.

## Project Conventions
- Never create a file without first checking INDEXSHORT.md to confirm it does not exist.
- Always follow naming conventions in CONVENTIONS.md.
- Log all work to PROMPT_[N]_IMPLEMENTATION.md before finishing.
- Update INDEX_FULL.md and INDEX_SHORT.md after every session.

## MCP Tool Usage (once RAG pipeline is installed)
- Use MCP tools only when the runtime supports native tool-calling for the selected model.
- If tool-calling is unavailable or unstable, continue in plain-language mode and do not output raw JSON tool-call stubs.
- Before balance work, prefer existing docs/logs if MCP tools are not available.
